title: American_Top_40_1975_February_1st
description:
"The biggest hits in the nation are yet to come as we count 'em down to a brand new number one."


American Top 40 with Casey Kasem aired on radio from July 4, 1970 until August 6, 1988. This recording is a rebroadcast from internet radio.

In this broadcast there is a band with an artist who, because of his flute-playing abilities, was voted number 1 in the category  of "other instruments" for the 3rd straight year in the Playboy Jazz and Pop poll.  

There is a song by a Canadian Group who was detained by US Customs for trying to smuggle bubble gum across the border.

There is a band whose nucleus goes back to 1964 when some of its members were in a group called Trade Winds.

There is a hit by the artist who, as of this countdown, had the biggest selling album by a solo performer in the history of recording.

A listener wants Casey to compare the chart action of Elton John's version of "Lucy In The Sky With Diamonds" with The Beatles' original. The response isn't what you'd expect.

The first artist to play with The Beatles and get label credit for it has a solo hit on the chart (and there are three former Beatles in this countdown).
